SIMPLE: exclusive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exclusive
<hw>Ex*clu"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>exclusif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the power of
preventing entrance; debarring from participation or enjoyment;
possessed and enjoyed to the exclusion of others; <as>as,
<ex>exclusive</ex> bars; <ex>exclusive</ex> privilege;
<ex>exclusive</ex> circles of society.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not taking into the account; excluding from
consideration; -- opposed to <contr>inclusive</contr>; <as>as, five
thousand troops, <ex>exclusive</ex> of artillery</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exclusive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Exclusive
<hw>Ex*clu"sive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of a coterie who exclude
others; one who from real of affected fastidiousness limits his
acquaintance to a select few.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exclusiveness</ent>⟦br⟧
